Tennis magazine selected Martina Navratilova as the greatest female tennis player for the years 1965 through 2005.[141][142] Tennis historian and journalist Bud Collins has called Navratilova "arguably, the greatest player of all time."[143] Billie Jean King said about Navratilova in 2006, "She's the greatest singles, doubles and mixed doubles player who's ever lived."[144]
